JOHANNESBURG - North West Premier Supra Mahumapelo says it is up to the ANC to tell him to step down. Pressure has been mounting on Mahumapelo to step down following allegations of corruption. READ: Hawks investigating Zuma, Mahumapelo cattle gift allegations Last week, protests flared up in Mahikeng forcing President Cyril Ramaphosa to cut short his trip to the Commonwealth Heads of Government Meeting in London. The ANC is expected to make a decision on Mahumapelo's future. eNCA